                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The script has some peculiar and archaic features:<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">
- Numeral ፮ “six” looks like compressed numeral ፯ “seven” (e.g., fols. 27rb l.9, 40vb l.19, 54r) but the numerals have dashes.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">
- Numeral ፩ is triangular and upwards oriented (e.g., fol. 5ra l.12, 18).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic">
- Vowel marker of ጵ is attached to the left of the top vertical stroke (fol. 5rc l.27).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic">
- Letters መ and ሠ are of smaller size.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h7" script="Ethiopic">
- Rather big loops.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h8" script="Ethiopic">
- The 6th order vowel marker of -s- (ስ) is sharply and strongly inclined to the left (cp. UhlPal 95).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
